Vice President Mike Pence spoke at the Parroquia Santa Bernadita church in Puerto Rico, expressing support and commitment to the people of Puerto Rico in their recovery efforts after Hurricane Maria. He conveyed President Trump's message that the United States will stand with Puerto Rico and help them rebuild. Pence commended Governor Rossello and Congresswoman Jennifer Gonzalez for their leadership, and praised the resilience and faith of the people of Puerto Rico. He also acknowledged the efforts of FEMA and the armed forces in providing assistance. Pence assured the people of Puerto Rico that the United States will continue to support them until they fully recover.